{"add":{"doc":{"id":"147975f08cbb9078c90a3d1fd06e691adee7d34beb8babf3e0378b36b86c5a8f","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Welles_declaration.jpg/150px-Welles_declaration.jpg","previous":[],"after":["The Welles declaration was issued on July 23, 1940 by acting United States Under Secretary of State Sumner Welles. The declaration condemned the Soviet Union's forcible incorporation of the Baltic states (Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania) and announced a U.S. refusal to recognize the legitimacy of Soviet control of the three states. It was an application of the Stimson Doctrine to the Baltic issue.The declaration was consistent with Franklin D. Roosevelt's overall attitude towards forcible territorial expansion, and reflected the views held by the highest levels of the Roosevelt administration."]}}}